Ebola haemorrhagic fever in Uganda - WHO Update 12
--------------------------------------------------
As of Sat 28 Oct 2000, the Ugandan Ministry of Health has reported 205 cases
of Ebola hemorrhagic fever, including 71 deaths.
As reported yesterday, Fri 27 Oct 2000, several organizations are
participating in the task forces in Gulu district and at the national level
to contain the outbreak. Two Italian epidemiologists will be joining the
team from the Istituto Superiore di SanitE0 (ISS) to further strengthen the
surveillance and field epidemiology activities in Gulu. UNICEF are assisting
with logistics and have supplied additional essential materials for case
management.
